{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'cd /home/daytona/workspace && rg -n \"swiftlint|swiftformat|qlty|secret|trufflehog|gitleaks|string audit|app store|xcodebuild\" apps/waketask-iphone -S'","aggregated_output":"apps/waketask-iphone/README.md:10:> **🚀 New user?** Read **[docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md](docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md)** (welcome + **App Store 4.3** checklist link + email you can send buyers). Then Mintlify **[Building Your App](/guides/building-your-app)** if you use the public docs site. For AI-assisted coding, keep **[docs/CLAUDE.md](docs/CLAUDE.md)** and root **[AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** handy.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:40:- [SwiftLint](https://github.com/realm/SwiftLint) — `brew install swiftlint` (optional, matches the CI lint job)\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:75:cp Config/Secrets.example.xcconfig Config/Secrets.xcconfig\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:80:Open `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` and replace the placeholder values:\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:116:**Important:** Every time you change `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`, you must run:\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:123:> **How it works:** Configuration.swift is committed with placeholder values for immediate clone-and-run. When you fill in real API keys, the update script reads Secrets.xcconfig and generates the production config. This approach is simple, reliable, and works in all build types.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:139:supabase secrets set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-YOUR_KEY\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:143:Get your function URL from the output and update `PROXY_BASE_URL` in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:157:- Set `PROXY_BASE_URL` and `PROXY_PATH` in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:216:│   └── Secrets.xcconfig           # API keys (gitignored)\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:224:### App Store guideline 4.3(a) — differentiate before you ship\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:293:2. Add credentials to `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:433:| Deploy | `/deploy` | App Store, TestFlight |\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:471:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:490:1. Check `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:501:3. Verify OpenRouter API key: `supabase secrets list`\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:532:4. Configure Supabase in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:540:1. Check `REVENUECAT_API_KEY` in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:549:2. Upload to App Store Connect\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:555:1. Complete App Store Connect listing\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:556:2. Create in-app purchases in App Store Connect\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:560:6. Update `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` with production URLs\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:1:# Hardcoded Secrets Scan Results\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:12:The project follows strong secrets management practices overall. `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` is gitignored. `Configuration.swift` is committed with only placeholder values. No real API keys, tokens, or passwords were found in committed source code.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:37:- **Risk**: None. This is the canonical example JWT from jwt.io, widely used in documentation and tests. The payload contains `{\"sub\":\"1234567890\",\"name\":\"John Doe\",\"iat\":1516239022}`. It is signed with the well-known secret \"secret\".\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:77:- **Risk**: None currently. Values are explicit placeholders. The `isConfigured()` function checks for \"placeholder\" and \"YOUR\" substrings to prevent accidental use. However, the `scripts/update-config.sh` script writes real values into this file, and if a developer forgets to check `.gitignore`, real secrets could be committed.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:82:### Finding 6: Risk of Real Secrets in Configuration.swift After update-config.sh\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:89:  The script reads `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` (gitignored) and writes real values directly into `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Generated/Configuration.swift` (committed). If a developer runs `bash scripts/update-config.sh` with real API keys in `Secrets.xcconfig`, then commits, real secrets will enter version control.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:134:### Finding 10: Config/Secrets.xcconfig Contains Partial URL Patterns\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:135:- **File**: `Config/Secrets.xcconfig:4,5,8,13`\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:145:- **Remediation**: Verify that the current values in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` are truly placeholders and not partial real values. The ellipsis format differs from the `Secrets.example.xcconfig` pattern (`YOUR_*`), which could confuse the `isConfigured()` validation logic.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:186:  supabase secrets set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-YOUR_KEY_HERE\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:197:1. **Secrets.xcconfig is gitignored** (`.gitignore` line 34) - Primary secrets file is properly excluded from version control.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:200:4. **AppLogger.redacted()** - Comprehensive PII/secret redaction in logging (tested for `sk-`, `pk-`, Bearer tokens, JWTs).\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:210:The single most significant risk is **Finding 6**: the `update-config.sh` script writes real secrets into a committed file (`Configuration.swift`). A developer who runs the script and then does `git add -A` or `git add .` will commit real API keys. This is a design tension between \"clone-and-run\" convenience and secret safety.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:24:**Positive findings:** The codebase demonstrates strong security fundamentals -- Keychain token storage, PII redaction in logs, RLS on all database tables, no hardcoded secrets in committed code, proxy architecture keeping API keys server-side, and type-safe deserialization throughout.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:174:| 12 | HS-006 | `update-config.sh` writes real secrets into committed `Configuration.swift` | `scripts/update-config.sh` |\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:202:| P1 | No hardcoded secrets in committed code | `Secrets.xcconfig` gitignored; `Configuration.swift` uses placeholders |\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:231:| **P3 (Next Sprint)** | HS-006: Pre-commit hook for Configuration.swift | 1 hr | Prevents secret leaks |\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:242:| `sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md` | Hardcoded secrets scan (12 findings) |\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/functions/ai/README.md:40:### 4. Set Secrets\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/functions/ai/README.md:44:supabase secrets set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/functions/ai/README.md:47:supabase secrets set APP_URL=https://your-app.com\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/functions/ai/README.md:133:- Set the secret: `supabase secrets set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=...`\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/architecture.md:14:| External services | OpenRouter (LLM API), RevenueCat, OneSignal, Apple App Store |\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/architecture.md:24:- **Storage**: SwiftData persistence for conversations/messages/settings, Keychain for secrets\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/architecture.md:75:5. **Config/Secrets <-> Binary**: Secrets loaded from `xcconfig` -> generated `Configuration.swift` with placeholders. Real values injected at build time.\napps/waketask-iphone/AGENTS.md:10:## App Store submission\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:124:      - Note the **Client ID** and **Client Secret**\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:133:      - **Client Secret**: Web OAuth Client Secret from Google\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:139:   Add the iOS Client ID to your `Secrets.xcconfig`:\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:177:## Step 7: Set Environment Secrets\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:181:supabase secrets set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-YOUR_KEY_HERE\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:184:supabase secrets set APP_URL=https://your-app.com\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:187:**Verify secrets:**\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:189:supabase secrets list\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:219:1. Open `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:284:- Check that `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` are correct in `Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:289:- Run: `supabase secrets set OPENROUTER_API_KEY=...`\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:290:- Verify with: `supabase secrets list`\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:315:  - [ ] Added GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID to Secrets.xcconfig\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:324:- [ ] Set OPENROUTER_API_KEY secret\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:10:- [ ] Set OpenRouter API key secret\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:12:- [ ] Updated `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` with correct values\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:70:- `OpenRouter API key not configured`: Set the secret\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:88:**Verify `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`:**\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:115:- Check that `PROXY_BASE_URL` is set in `Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:244:- [ ] Secrets set in Supabase (not exposed)\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:280:1. Check `PROXY_BASE_URL` is set in `Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask