etask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:363:- **Config:** `PROXY_BASE_URL` and `PROXY_PATH` in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`. When empty, the app uses `EchoLLMClient` automatically.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:467:- Committing secrets (check .gitignore)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:544:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:773:// Don't set PROXY_BASE_URL in Config/Secrets.xcconfig\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:864:**Use SwiftFormat/SwiftLint rules:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:878:- **Skills** (`.agents/skills/`): General iOS/SwiftUI best practices — debugging, testing, App Store guidelines, performance profiling\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:884:- Apple Skills Collection — App Store, testing, generators, product lifecycle\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:894:- [docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md](buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md) - Buyer welcome + App Store 4.3 link + email template\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:927:4. **Add to .gitignore:** If it has secrets\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:7:## Before your first App Store upload (required)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:9:**App Store Guideline 4.3(a)** rejects apps that look like undifferentiated template spam (similar **binary**, **metadata**, or **concept** to other submissions). Using this codebase is fine; shipping it **without** meaningful differentiation is not.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:23:3. Follow **`README.md`** → configure `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` when you are ready for real Auth / AI / Payments.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:31:**Subject:** SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro — your download + one thing before the App Store\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:44:Required before your first App Store submission:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:63:| [`docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md`](../BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md) | Boilerplate → App Store journey |\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Profile/ProfileSubscriptionSection.swift:5:/// \"Subscription\" section showing active plan + App Store Guideline 3.1.1\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/README.md:3:- **[POST_PURCHASE.md](POST_PURCHASE.md)** — Welcome, App Store **4.3** checklist link, and copy-paste post-purchase email for your delivery zip.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:46:Configure in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:90:# Don't set PROXY_BASE_URL in Config/Secrets.xcconfig\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:454:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:569:1. Check OpenRouter API key in Supabase secrets:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:571:   supabase secrets list\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:585:1. Set `PROXY_BASE_URL` in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LegalDocumentView.swift:169:- Refunds are handled in accordance with Apple's App Store refund policies\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LegalDocumentView.swift:171:- You may request a refund through the App Store within the time frame specified by Apple\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/LegalDocumentView.swift:193:For App Store-related issues, please contact Apple Support directly.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Feature.Chat.md:507:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Core.md:235:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:3:Smart, sentiment-based app rating prompt system. Tracks positive and negative user actions, calculates a sentiment score with time decay, and shows a configurable pre-prompt popup before triggering the native App Store review dialog.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:144:    let acceptTitle: String            // \"Rate on App Store\"\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:281:By default, the module **permanently stops asking** once a user taps \"Rate on App Store\" in the pre-prompt popup. This is controlled by the `stopAskingAfterRating` config flag.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:285:Apple's `SKStoreReviewController.requestReview()` does **not** provide any callback or return value indicating whether the user actually left a review. There is also no App Store API to check if a specific user has reviewed your app. This means:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:288:- Tapping \"Rate on App Store\" is the **best available signal** that the user intended to leave a review\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:291:So when the user taps \"Rate on App Store\" in the pre-prompt, the engine sets a `userHasRated` flag in storage. On subsequent calls to `shouldPrompt()`, if `stopAskingAfterRating` is `true` and `userHasRated` is `true`, the method returns `false` immediately -- no matter how high the score gets.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Auth.md:67:Configure in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Auth.md:237:**Note:** The boilerplate uses the native `SignInWithAppleButton` from `AuthenticationServices` to comply with Apple's Human Interface Guidelines and App Store requirements. Always use this native button, never custom-styled alternatives.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Auth.md:508:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:18:- In-app purchase configuration (App Store Connect)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:58:Configure in `Config/Secrets.xcconfig`:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:214:1. Create products in App Store Connect\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:255:1. Create in-app purchase in App Store Connect (type: Non-Consumable)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:308:# Config/Secrets.xcconfig\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:402:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Payments.md:477:1. Check App Store Connect:\nap