 only. Hosted macOS simulator traversal has not run, and allow_macos_deferred=false forbids treating this as pass evidence.\"\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:5:> **Toolchain requirement.** This boilerplate is on **Swift 6 strict concurrency** with **Xcode 26.2+** and the **iOS 26 SDK** (Liquid Glass). `Packages/*/Package.swift` is pinned to `swift-tools-version: 6.2`; the Xcode project uses `SWIFT_VERSION = 6.0`. Runtime still supports iOS 17+ via a SwiftUI `Material` fallback built into `SAIGlass`. See `RELEASE_NOTES.md` for the full v2.0.0 scope.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:109:1. **Read** [docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md) — branding map, `strings` audit, module removal, Review Notes template.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:896:- [RELEASE_NOTES.md](../RELEASE_NOTES.md) - v2.0.0 release notes (Swift 6, Liquid Glass)\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:296:This is a **compile-time** check. In RELEASE builds, the `shouldUseMock` variable is hard-coded to `false` and the mock auth code is stripped by the compiler. The `AUTH_BYPASS` environment variable cannot affect production builds.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:302:### BL-012: Environment Variable Feature Flags in Release Builds\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:307:In RELEASE builds, feature flags like `DIAGNOSTICS_ENABLED`, `CRASHLYTICS_ENABLED`, and `CHAT_SYNC_ENABLED` are read from `ProcessInfo.processInfo.environment`. While environment variables cannot typically be set on a production iOS device (they require Xcode scheme configuration or jailbreak), this pattern is unconventional. On jailbroken devices, environment variables could theoretically be injected at launch.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:311:**Impact:** Minimal. No security-sensitive flags exposed via environment variables in release mode.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:314:Consider using compile-time flags (`#if`) or server-driven feature flags for release builds instead of environment variables.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:335:### BL-014: PROXY_DEFAULT_HEADERS from Environment in Release Builds\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/businesslogic-results.md:351:Wrap in `#if DEBUG` or remove environment-based header injection for release builds.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:13:→ **[APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](../checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:15:That checklist covers: Release **`strings`** audit on your `.app`, where to rebrand, removing dead demo files from the app target, module removal, and App Review Notes. Prompt pack: [`docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md`](../prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:25:5. **Before submit:** complete the hardening checklist above.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:45:→ docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:47:Apple sometimes flags “template similarity” (Guideline 4.3). That guide walks you through a Release binary audit, rebranding, metadata, and what to remove if you drop modules (e.g. chat/AI).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:49:If anything fails to build, check Xcode version (26.2+) and RELEASE_NOTES.md.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:64:| [`docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md`](../recipes/WhiteLabeling.md) | Rebrand (pair with 4.3 checklist) |\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/README.md:3:- **[POST_PURCHASE.md](POST_PURCHASE.md)** — Welcome, App Store **4.3** checklist link, and copy-paste post-purchase email for your delivery zip.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/hardcodedsecrets-results.md:174:- **Risk**: MEDIUM. These placeholders are guarded by `#if DEBUG` and an environment variable check, so they will not appear in release builds. However, in debug builds with `AUTH_BYPASS=1`, the app connects to `https://placeholder.supabase.co` with a fake key. If someone registers `placeholder.supabase.co`, they could potentially intercept debug auth requests. More practically, this is a development convenience pattern that is safe if developers understand it.\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:190:| 21 | BL-014 | `PROXY_DEFAULT_HEADERS` read from env in release | `CompositionRoot.swift:429` |\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/final-report.md:210:| P9 | Debug mock auth gated by `#if DEBUG` | Compile-time guard, not present in release builds |\napps/waketask-iphone/sast/architecture.md:19:Modular monolith iOS app using local Swift packages for separation of concerns. Single app target (`SwiftAIBoilerplatePro`) with a `CompositionRoot` for dependency injection. All modules communicate through protocols, enabling mock/real swapping (e.g., `MockAuthClient` in DEBUG, real `SessionManager` in RELEASE).\napps/waketask-iphone/AGENTS.md:12:- Before the first upload (or after a **Guideline 4.3** rejection), follow **`docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md`** — Release binary `strings` audit, branding locations, metadata, module removal, and Review Notes. Buyers often forget **dead Swift files** still compiled into the app target; scrub template literals (`SwiftAI`, `Boilerplate`, demo copy).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:5:> The Supabase Edge Function that backs `ProxyLLMClient` is now authenticated-only, with a model allowlist (`openai/gpt-3.5-turbo`, `openai/gpt-4o-mini`), message count + length bounds, a server-controlled system prompt, temperature clamping, and sanitized errors. Memory context is now injected as a separate delimited message rather than appended to the user's text. Details in `RELEASE_NOTES.md` and the v2.0.0 Supabase migration docs.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Feature.Chat.md:937:- ✅ Works flawlessly in Debug and Release builds\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:269:## Customization Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Auth.md:116:**RELEASE builds:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/HomeViewModule.md:538:## Testing Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Accessibility.md:206:### Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Accessibility.md:209:A11yChecklist.printChecklist()\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Localization.md:500:### Testing Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Storage.md:7:> **v2.0 — `@MainActor` repositories.** `MessageRepositoryImpl`, `ConversationRepositoryImpl`, and `SettingsRepositoryImpl` are now pinned to `@MainActor` (P0 data-race fix). `ModelContext` is not thread-safe, and the old `nonisolated(unsafe)` annotation has been removed. **Creating or calling these repositories from non-main code requires `await`.** Public APIs and method signatures are unchanged — only the isolation is. `SupabaseMessageRepository.page()` now filters by `user_id` for defense-in-depth against the IDOR fix shipped in the same release.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Storage.md:566:3. Test migrations before release:\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/maintenance/ReleaseProcess.md:1:# Release Process\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/maintenance/ReleaseProcess.md:3:This document describes how we prepare, version, and publish releases.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/maintenance/ReleaseProcess.md:16:5. Tag the release in git: `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push --tags`\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/maintenance/Changelog.md:3:All notable changes to this project will be documented here. See `docs/maintenance/ReleaseProcess.md` for process and estimation method.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/maintenance/Changelog.md:18:## [Unreleased]\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPage.swift:46:            systemImage: \"checklist.checked\",\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/README.md:14:## Safety Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/README.md:24:- [ ] **If preparing App Store submission:** No template fingerprints in Release binary — see [APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](../checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md) and [AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md](AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md:5:**Prerequisite reading (in this boilerplate):** [APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](../checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md:16:Read the boilerplate checklist mindset (binary similarity + metadata + concept):\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md:17:- Remove template strings from the **Release** binary (unused Swift files still compile in).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md:26:5. Give me a **post-build verification** shell recipe using `strings` on the Release .app binary.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md:43:3. Give an ordered checklist: SPM → CompositionRoot → Views → tests → config secrets.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:30:8. [Launch Checklist](#launch-checklist)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1369:**Manual testing checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1423:Apple rejects **spam / template similarity** when your **binary, metadata, or primary concept** looks too close to other apps. Complete **[checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** before upload: Release `strings` audit, branding map, module removal notes, Review Notes template. Prompt pack: **[prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md](prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md)**.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1559:## Launch Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1561:### Pre-Submission Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1612:### Build for Release\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1727:**Checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1745:#### 4. Configure Build Settings for Release\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1750:- Verify Release = \"Optimize for Speed [-O]\"\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1752:- Verify Release = \"DWARF with dSYM\"\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1762:- Release hotfix if needed\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md:1780:- Release updates regularly (every 2-4 weeks ideal)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/examples/AccessibilityExamples.swift:376:// Print the checklist to console\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/examples/AccessibilityExamples.swift:377:func runAccessibilityChecklist() {\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/examples/AccessibilityExamples.swift:378:    A11yChecklist.printChecklist()\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/examples/AccessibilityExamples.swift:380:    // 📋 Accessibility Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/UpstreamSync.md:107:Best when you want all changes from a release.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/UpstreamSync.md:285:A: The boilerplate is a commercial product. If you find bugs, email berkinsili@gmail.com and they'll be fixed in the next release.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/AppIconsAndBranding.md:151:### Visual Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/AppIconsAndBranding.md:160:### Technical Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/Theming.md:145:## Theme Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md:3:> **App Store 4.3(a):** Rebranding is necessary but not sufficient. After white-labeling, run the [APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](../checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md) checklist (binary `strings` audit, metadata, removing dead template files from the app target).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md:5:Complete checklist for rebranding this boilerplate as your own app.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md:164:## Quick Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md:210:See: `BUILDING_YOUR_APP.md` for complete launch checklist.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:5:> **Toolchain:** v2.0.0 requires **Xcode 26.2+** and the iOS 26 SDK. The workspace is on **Swift 6** strict concurrency across all 11 SPM packages. Runtime still supports iOS 17+ via the SwiftUI `Material` fallback inside `SAIGlass`. See [RELEASE_NOTES.md](../RELEASE_NOTES.md) for the full v2.0.0 scope.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:32:- [POST_PURCHASE.md](buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md) — Welcome, **first App Store upload** checklist link, copy-paste email for your delivery workflow\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:76:## Checklists\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:77:Verification checklists for complex integrations.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:79:- [REVENUECAT_INTEGRATION.md](checklists/REVENUECAT_INTEGRATION.md) - Complete RevenueCat setup verification\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:80:- [APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md) - **Guideline 4.3(a)** template/spam differentiation: binary audit, branding map, module removal, Review Notes\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:85:- [1.0.0.md](migrations/1.0.0.md) - Initial release notes\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:86:- **v2.0.0** — see [RELEASE_NOTES.md](../RELEASE_NOTES.md) and the [v2.0.0 handoff pack](release/v2.0.0/INDEX.md) for the Swift 6 / Liquid Glass migration. Downstream forks applying v2.0: run the Supabase migration `20260408000000_fix_conversation_stats_auth.sql` and redeploy the `ai` edge function — see [integrations/Supabase.md](integrations/Supabase.md).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:91:- [WhiteLabeling.md](recipes/WhiteLabeling.md) - Complete rebranding checklist (pair with [4.3 hardening](checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md) before App Store submission)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:98:Release process, changelog, and estimation methodology.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/INDEX.md:101:- [ReleaseProcess.md](maintenance/ReleaseProcess.md) - Release workflow and estimations\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/Supabase.md:5:> **v2.0.0 required migration + edge-function redeploy.** Upgrading a downstream fork from v1.9 → v2.0 **must** apply migration `supabase/migrations/20260408000000_fix_conversation_stats_auth.sql` and redeploy the `ai` edge function. The migration fixes a SQL IDOR (the `get_conversation_with_stats` RPC now requires `c.user_id = auth.uid()`); the redeployed edge function enforces the v2.0 model allowlist, message size bounds, temperature clamping, server-controlled system prompt, and sanitized error responses. Skipping either step leaves you on the pre-v2.0 security posture. See [v2.0.0 upgrade steps](../../RELEASE_NOTES.md#upgrading-from-v19x) for the full checklist.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/Supabase.md:339:## Production Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/RevenueCat.md:427:## Production Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Generated/Configuration.swift:8:/// This ensures configs work in all build types (Debug, Release, Archive, TestFlight, App Store)\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:1:# Release notes (draft) — next version\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:3:**Status:** Draft — **not shipped**. Replace this file’s content into `RELEASE_NOTES.md` (or merge sections) when you cut the git tag and GitHub release. Set the shipped date and final version number below.\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:12:1. **App Store Guideline 4.3(a) playbook** — First-party checklist for “template spam” rejections: Release **binary `strings` audit**, branding map, metadata, Review Notes template, and **per-module removal** guidance (including the **FeatureChat ↔ AI** coupling).\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:23:| Checklist | `docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md` |\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:27:| Recipes | `docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md` callout → 4.3 checklist |\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:28:| Prompts index | `docs/prompts/README.md` safety checklist + 4.3 prompts |\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:29:| Package READMEs | All 11 packages: “Shipping your own app (App Store 4.3)” footer → checklist |\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:40:## Not in this release\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:43:- GitHub **Releases** / tags: create when you finalize the version number and marketing.\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:47:## Checklist before you tag\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:49:- [ ] Move/rename this draft into `RELEASE_NOTES.md` (or append after v2.0.0 section).\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:50:- [ ] Collapse `CHANGELOG.md` **`[Unreleased]`** into a dated **`[x.y.z]`** section.\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md:52:- [ ] Publish GitHub Release with the same body as the top section of `RELEASE_NOTES.md`.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/ChatSync.md:565:**Checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/Crashlytics.md:67:    return true   // Already enabled in RELEASE\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/Crashlytics.md:273:**Checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/Crashlytics.md:276:- [ ] App built in RELEASE mode\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/ProfilePhotos.md:420:**Checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/OneSignal.md:361:**Checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/integrations/OneSignal.md:383:**Checklist:**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/foundations/TestingStrategy.md:393:Running `swift test` inside `Packages/<PackageName>` is **not supported** — iOS-only SwiftUI packages cannot compile against the macOS host toolchain, which is why the v2.0 CI drop removed the `package-tests` matrix. Package code is exercised by the app test suite (`xcodebuild test` on an iOS 26.2 simulator). If you need to run a package in isolation, create a host target inside a test plan instead.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/foundations/TestingStrategy.md:436:## Summary Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/foundations/Composition.md:70:**Simple, reliable, no build phases or complexity.** Works in ALL build types (Debug, Release, Archive, TestFlight, App Store).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/foundations/Architecture.md:5:> **Toolchain.** v2.0.0 ships on **Swift 6** (strict concurrency) and **Xcode 26.2+** with the **iOS 26 SDK**. All 11 SPM packages are pinned to `swift-tools-version: 6.2`. Runtime still supports iOS 17+ via the SwiftUI `Material` fallback built into `SAIGlass`. See [RELEASE_NOTES.md](../../RELEASE_NOTES.md) for the full v2.0.0 scope.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/foundations/Architecture.md:89:**RELEASE builds:** Always use real auth\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md:3:This checklist helps you **ship an app that is clearly your product**, not an undifferentiated copy of SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro. Apple cites **Guideline 4.3(a)** when an app’s **binary, metadata, and/or concept** look too similar to other submissions (including other template-based apps).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md:5:**This is not legal advice.** It is an engineering and product checklist aligned with common App Review patterns.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md:15:| **Binary** — shared literals, unused views, identical branding strings | Audit with `strings` on a **Release** build; delete dead Swift files from the app target |\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md:26:1. **Archive** with a **Release** configuration (not Debug).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/REVENUECAT_INTEGRATION.md:1:# RevenueCat Integration Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/REVENUECAT_INTEGRATION.md:3:Use this checklist to verify your RevenueCat integration is complete and working.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/checklists/REVENUECAT_INTEGRATION.md:223:## Production Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/migrations/1.0.0.md:4:Initial release with unified authentication, two-tier documentation, and production-ready AI chat.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/migrations/1.0.0.md:16:None (initial release)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/migrations/1.0.0.md:28:Not applicable (initial release)\napps/waketask-iphone/DISTRIBUTION_README.md:176:### RELEASE Mode (Production)\napps/waketask-iphone/DISTRIBUTION_README.md:213:## ✅ Pre-Launch Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:1:# Release Notes — v2.0.0 (Swift 6 & iOS 26 Liquid Glass)\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:36:### Migration notes retained for next release\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:145:The `v1.9.0` tag is the supported line for teams that cannot move off Xcode 15/16 yet. We'll accept critical security patches on a `release/1.9` branch but will not backport new features.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Localization/README.md:84:If you **replace** this module with String Catalogs or another i18n approach, migrate all `L10n` call sites. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: Localization**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Networking/README.md:150:If you **remove** HTTP needs entirely, see **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: Networking** for `CompositionRoot`, interceptors, and clients that depend on `HTTPClient`.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/FeatureSettings/README.md:36:Settings and paywall surfaces are central to most forks. If you **strip** this package, replace navigation to `SettingsView` / `PaywallView` and reimplement account/legal URLs. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: FeatureSettings**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/AI/README.md:290:This module **depends on FeatureChat** for `LLMClient` / `LLMMessage` (re-exported from `AI.swift`). If you **remove chat** but keep AI, you must **move those types** and update `Package.swift` — see **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: AI** and **Removing: FeatureChat**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Auth/README.md:191:If you **remove or replace** auth, update `LaunchRouter`, sign-in views, Keychain token wiring on `HTTPClient`, and settings account UI. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: Auth**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Core/README.md:118:If you **heavily customize** this package (e.g. `AppLogger.subsystem` fallback strings), or **remove** others that depend on Core, see **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — especially the binary audit and **Removing: Core** notes.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage/README.md:157:If you **drop models or repositories**, update `Schema([...])` in `CompositionRoot` and every caller. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: Storage**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Payments/README.md:164:If you **remove subscriptions**, strip `PaymentsClient` from `CompositionRoot`, paywall surfaces in `FeatureSettings` / root views, and RevenueCat config keys. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: Payments**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/FeatureRating/README.md:40:If you **remove** rating prompts, delete `RatingClient` wiring from `CompositionRoot` and remove `.ratingPrompt()` (or equivalent) from the root view. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: FeatureRating**.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yAudit.swift:207:// MARK: - Accessibility Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yAudit.swift:208:/// Quick reference checklist for developers\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yAudit.swift:209:public enum A11yChecklist {\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yAudit.swift:223:    public static func printChecklist() {\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11yAudit.swift:224:        print(\"\\n📋 Accessibility Checklist\")\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/FeatureChat/README.md:259:`LLMClient` and `LLMMessage` are defined **here**; the **AI** package re-exports this module. If you **remove chat**, you must relocate those types or drop AI entirely. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: FeatureChat**.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:10:> **🚀 New user?** Read **[docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md](docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md)** (welcome + **App Store 4.3** checklist link + email you can send buyers). Then Mintlify **[Building Your App](/guides/building-your-app)** if you use the public docs site. For AI-assisted coding, keep **[docs/CLAUDE.md](docs/CLAUDE.md)** and root **[AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** handy.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:42:> **Using older Xcode?** Stay on the [`v1.9.0`](https://github.com/yourusername/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/releases/tag/v1.9.0) tag until you can upgrade. v2.0+ uses iOS 26 SDK symbols that older toolchains cannot compile, regardless of `#available` checks.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:185:**RELEASE builds:**\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:226:Apple may reject apps that look like **undifferentiated template uploads** (similar binary, metadata, or concept to other submissions). After you rebrand, run the checklist in **[`docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md`](docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** (`strings` audit on Release builds, remove dead demo files from the app target, module removal map) and use the prompts in **[`docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md`](docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md)**. AI assistants should read **[`docs/CLAUDE.md`](docs/CLAUDE.md)** for the same guidance.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:524:1. Verify you're running a DEBUG build (not RELEASE)\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:525:2. Check scheme configuration (should be Debug, not Release)\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:548:1. Archive for release: Product → Archive\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:563:**Checklist:** See `docs/migrations/supabase.md` and `docs/migrations/revenuecat.md`\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Materials/SAIGlass.swift:54:    /// available and falls back to SwiftUI `Material` on earlier releases.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Materials/SAIGlass.swift:110:    /// content stays legible. On earlier releases this is a no-op.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Materials/SAIGlass.swift:132:    /// No-op on earlier releases.\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Materials/SAIGlass.swift:148:    /// remaining a tab bar on iPhone. No-op on earlier releases.\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md:304:## Production Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/README.md:50:You will almost always **keep** DesignSystem; differentiate via `BrandConfig`, colors, and components. Wholesale removal requires replacing all `DSColors` / `DSSpacing` usage. See **[APP_STORE 4.3 hardening](../../docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)** — **Removing: DesignSystem**.\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:5:## Pre-Testing Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:239:### Phase 4: Production Readiness\napps/waketask-iphone/supabase/TESTING_GUIDE.md:241:#### 4.1 Security Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh:4:REPORT_PATH=\"reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json\"\napps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh:8:# The real hosted macOS Appium/XCUITest traversal must replace this skeleton in the iOS validation phase.\napps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh:17:    \