/CHANGELOG.md:5:## [Unreleased]\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:9:- **App Store 4.3(a)** — `docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md` (binary audit, branding map, metadata, Review Notes, module removal, AI↔FeatureChat note); `docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md`\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:11:- **Agent discovery** — root `AGENTS.md`; `RELEASE_NOTES_NEXT.md` (draft narrative for the next Git tag)\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:27:Full Swift 6 migration, iOS 26 SDK readiness, and first-class Liquid Glass\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:53:  - `.saiGlass(_:in:interactive:)` view modifier — the one call site adopts Liquid Glass on iOS 26 and stays visually consistent on earlier releases\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:124:- **Supabase** — Apply migration `20260408000000_fix_conversation_stats_auth.sql` and deploy the updated `ai` edge function on every backend that ships this release\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:152:- Updated `DISTRIBUTION_CHECKLIST.md` with 11-package count, skills verification phase, and email distribution\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:156:- Email task added to `DISTRIBUTION_CHECKLIST.md`\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:161:- `DISTRIBUTION_CHECKLIST.md` now includes Phase 4.5 for skills verification\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:201:- `docs/modules/FeatureRating.md` -- complete module guide with API reference, examples by app type, and customization checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/CHANGELOG.md:491:- Visual guide includes token reference tables and accessibility checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:5:> **Toolchain requirement.** This boilerplate is on **Swift 6 strict concurrency** with **Xcode 26.2+** and the **iOS 26 SDK** (Liquid Glass). `Packages/*/Package.swift` is pinned to `swift-tools-version: 6.2`; the Xcode project uses `SWIFT_VERSION = 6.0`. Runtime still supports iOS 17+ via a SwiftUI `Material` fallback built into `SAIGlass`. See `RELEASE_NOTES.md` for the full v2.0.0 scope.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:109:1. **Read** [docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md) — branding map, `strings` audit, module removal, Review Notes template.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/CLAUDE.md:896:- [RELEASE_NOTES.md](../RELEASE_NOTES.md) - v2.0.0 release notes (Swift 6, Liquid Glass)\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:13:→ **[APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md](../checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md)**\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:15:That checklist covers: Release **`strings`** audit on your `.app`, where to rebrand, removing dead demo files from the app target, module removal, and App Review Notes. Prompt pack: [`docs/prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md`](../prompts/AppStore4_3Hardening.prompts.md).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:25:5. **Before submit:** complete the hardening checklist above.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:45:→ docs/checklists/APP_STORE_4_3_HARDENING.md\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:47:Apple sometimes flags “template similarity” (Guideline 4.3). That guide walks you through a Release binary audit, rebranding, metadata, and what to remove if you drop modules (e.g. chat/AI).\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:49:If anything fails to build, check Xcode version (26.2+) and RELEASE_NOTES.md.\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/POST_PURCHASE.md:64:| [`docs/recipes/WhiteLabeling.md`](../recipes/WhiteLabeling.md) | Rebrand (pair with 4.3 checklist) |\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/buyers/README.md:3:- **[POST_PURCHASE.md](POST_PURCHASE.md)** — Welcome, App Store **4.3** checklist link, and copy-paste post-purchase email for your delivery zip.\napps/waketask-iphone/skills-lock.json:869:    \"release-review\": {\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/AI.md:5:> The Supabase Edge Function that backs `ProxyLLMClient` is now authenticated-only, with a model allowlist (`openai/gpt-3.5-turbo`, `openai/gpt-4o-mini`), message count + length bounds, a server-controlled system prompt, temperature clamping, and sanitized errors. Memory context is now injected as a separate delimited message rather than appended to the user's text. Details in `RELEASE_NOTES.md` and the v2.0.0 Supabase migration docs.\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcscheme:87:      buildConfiguration = \"Release\"\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcscheme:107:      buildConfiguration = \"Release\"\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/Feature.Chat.md:937:- ✅ Works flawlessly in Debug and Release builds\napps/waketask-iphone/docs/modules/FeatureRating.md:269:## Customization Checklist\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:85:\t\t949AD4AD2EA3B3F9007FE07E /* ReleaseProcess.md */ = {isa = PBXFileReference; lastKnownFileType = net.daringfireball.markdown; path = ReleaseProcess.md; sourceTree = \"<group>\"; };\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:289:\t\t\t\t949AD4AD2EA3B3F9007FE07E /* ReleaseProcess.md */,\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:672:\t\t943304FB2E6628CA008485E6 /* Release */ = {\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:730:\t\t\tname = Release;\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:770:\t\t943304FE2E6628CA008485E6 /* Release */ = {\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:806:\t\t\tname = Release;\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:829:\t\t943305012E6628CA008485E6 /* Release */ = {\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:848:\t\t\tname = Release;\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj:869:\t\t943305042E6628CA008485E6 /* Release */ = {\napps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj/project.pb